node.text:
By law, credit repair companies can only charge you fees for credit repair services that have already been provided. As stated in the Credit Repair Organizations Act:⁣
⁣
“No credit repair organization may charge or receive any money or other valuable consideration for the performance of any service which the credit repair organization has agreed to perform for any consumer before such service is fully performed.”⁣
⁣
In other words, you should avoid any credit repair company that asks you to pay “advance” or “upfront” fees before they have completed the work that you are paying for.⁣
⁣
I am constantly being asked why I do not support tradelines and that is one of the main reasons why! It's disgusting that there are people out here preying on those who are really trying to improve their lives. .⁣
⁣
There are a lot of fly by night credit repair companies out here. Some of these credit repair companies are actually identity thieves. They will repair your credit and either use it for themselves, sell your personal information so that other thieves can steal your identity, or apply for credit cards in your name so that they can sell them as tradelines. And of course you have some credit repair companies that just want to take your money!⁣
⁣
There is no quick fix to repairing your credit! Please be mindful that the moment you hand over your social security number, you have given someone access to your life. .⁣
⁣
This is one of the many reasons why I am very protective of my clients' information, the people I hire, and the type of systems I operate off of. .⁣
⁣
There are some really good credit repair companies out there and there are some horrible ones! Research and use your gut!

node.text:
Due to the pandemic, millions of consumers are facing tough financial hardships…and now so has their credit.⁣
⁣
The CFPB has given the credit bureaus “flexibility” which means they will not be enforcing the credit bureaus to investigate consumer disputes within accordance of the FCRA. This means as of now, the credit bureaus will NOT be forced to investigate consumer disputes.⁣
⁣
The credit bureaus were also granted an additional 15 days to complete dispute investigation.⁣
⁣
We at AMB Credit Consultants are taking extreme measures to ensure that the credit bureaus follow up with our clients’ disputes and have put in place proactive follow up responses to reinform the credit bureaus of not just their legal obligation but their moral obligation to safeguard the accuracy of consumer credit reports.⁣
⁣
As of now, our methods have been effective and no action from our clients is needed. Our mission is to be your voice and to make sure your credit reputation is accurate and favorable.⁣
⁣
We will continue to get through this pandemic together while continuing to make sure your consumer rights are no longer violated and that your credit reports report 100% accurate information within accordance of the law.⁣
⁣
Thank you for allowing us to be a part of your credit journey,⁣
⁣
Team AMB Credit

I was one of those females and after living paycheck to paycheck, getting payday loans, nsf fees, overdraft fees, having bad credit, no budget, poor money habits, and lack of financial knowledge...I said no more!⁣⁣
⁣⁣
After finally getting my financial life in order things changed for the better and the experience was LUXURIOUS! ⁣⁣
⁣⁣
I wanted everyone to experience this! Especially women! ......BLACK women!⁣⁣
⁣⁣
I never thought my passion for credit education and financial literacy would lead me to where I am now. Never thought I’d able to help hundreds of thousands of people reach their credit goals and get a second chance at financial stability.⁣⁣
⁣⁣
I’m honored, blessed, grateful and so appreciative! It also let me know that there’s so much more work to do and I’m with it!⁣⁣
⁣⁣
Also, here’s a reminder: It’s okay to start from the bottom because when it’s up...IT’S UP!⁣⁣
⁣⁣
Check out my WFAA feature! ⁣⁣
⁣⁣
And many thanks to those who support me! I’m honored.⁣⁣
⁣⁣

node.text:
A time barred debt is a debt that can still be collected on due to it being unpaid, HOWEVER…you are not legally bound to pay it due to it being past the statute of limitations.⁣
⁣
Depending on which state you reside deciphers the statue of limitations. For example, in Florida it is five years. Texas is four years, Georgia is six years. A quick Google search and you can see the statute of limitations for time barred debts in your state.⁣
⁣
Now here’s where people go WRONG!! When a collection agency comes after you over a time barred debt, IF YOU PAY OR EVEN AGREE TO PAY, YOU ARE NOW LEGALLY BOUND TO THE DEBT AND YOU ARE RESPONSIBLE FOR PAYING IT OR YOU COULD GET SUED!⁣
⁣
A collection agency attempted to go after my cousin for a time barred debt and she ALMOST PAID IT. Luckily, she had me on her team. I wrote a dispute letter that demanded the collection agency cease all collection activity, remove the collection account from her credit report, and do not resell the debt! The collection agency responded and agreed!⁣
⁣
This live is going to show you how to deal with collection agencies when they attempt to come after you behind a time barred debt.⁣
⁣
If you want a copy of the Time Barred Debt Dispute Letter I used, click the link in bio and get on my email list.

This is a long but VERY educational live, grab your pen and notepad to watch! If you watched, what did you learn? Comment Below.

node.title: How the FICO Score Really Works!

node.text:
Only 3 states do not allow insurance companies to use credit scores to determine rates: California, Hawaii, and Massachusetts. The rest of us have to deal with the fact that lower credit scores mean higher premiums. 

This is another cost to factor in when you're shopping around for a new car. A low credit score means a higher car payment AND higher insurance premium, combined these make owning a vehicle that much more expensive.

node.text:
Don't be surprised if a lender says you have a different score than what you pulled on Credit Karma (or Credit Sesame or even the FICO score your bank gives you).⠀
⠀
It's not that Credit Karma isn't wrong, per se. It's just not what lenders use. Part of it is because of legal requirements for mortgages and part of it is because FICO has such a strong hold on the credit score industry.⠀
⠀
The key is to have your credit in the best shape possible before applying for a loan so your credit score is good no matter which one your lender uses. This means no recent late payments. A low credit utilization. And ideally, no outstanding collections or charge-offs.

node.accessibility_caption: Photo by Luxurious Credit on August 10, 2021. May be an image of text that says 'What can restart the clock on a collection account? Admitting the debt belongs to you or the amount owed is correct. Making a payment, even a small partial payment. ! Setting up a payment arrangement. Promising to make a payment. LuxuriousCredit'.

node.text:
You don't have a contract with a collection agency unless you create one. That's their goal. They have scripts that tell them what to say to you. They have information about you from your credit report and other reporting sources. Some even have a score that tells them whether you're likely to pay.⠀
⠀
It's not about whether you had an unpaid balance with the mall jewelry store back in 2016. It's about what is legally enforceable in a court.

node.text:
Don't wait until it's 45 days before your lease is up to check your credit score because you've decided you want to buy a house instead of renting again. Or until you *need* to buy a new car asap because your old one is about to quit.⠀
⠀
The sooner you start working on your credit, the more time you have to get your credit in the best shape possible. The higher your credit score, the more room you have to negotiate. You can shop around for the best offers instead of accepting whatever you can qualify for.⠀
⠀
If it's been awhile since you last checked your credit score or report, this is your sign that it's time to check in.
